<subSubSection id="C34C72A24B1CFF9F14F9D43FFEA5FEEF" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE921294B1CFF9214F9D43FFA87F94E" blockId="7.[136,1452,1382,2057]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF92152ED43FFCE9FA6F" authority="(Trabaud 1906: 154)" baseAuthorityName="Trabaud" baseAuthorityPageNumber="154" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[351,777,1382,1409]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marocana">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF92152ED43FFDF7FA6E" box="[351,535,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Abies marocana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1CFF921657D43FFCE1FA6F" author="Trabaud, L." box="[550,769,1382,1409]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" pagination="154 - 155" refId="ref11773" refString="Trabaud, L. (1906) Sur la presence d'un Abies nouveau au Maroc (Abies marocana). Bulletin de la Societe botanique de France 53: 154 - 155. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00378941.1906.10831158" type="journal article" year="1906">Trabaud 1906: 154</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
includes a diagnosis in French “Feuilles aiguës, épaisses à la base, plus larges et plus longues que dans l’ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF9216E4D4D2FCF1FA4A" authorityName="Antoine" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[661,785,1419,1445]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinsapo">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF9216E4D4D2FD46FA4B" box="[661,678,1419,1445]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF9216C4D4D2FCF1FA4A" box="[693,785,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Pinsapo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ne se tordant pas à la base pour infléchir sur les rameaux, hypoderme double, stomates sur les deux faces de la feuille, mais en moindre quantité sur la face supérieure; glandes résinifères sur l’hypoderme inférieur; còne non vu”, followed by a locality, date and collector (“Les montagnes du sud de Tétuan, à Chechaouen 
<date id="FFE807E94B1CFF921593D4AFFD91F9FE" box="[482,625,1526,1552]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" value="1906-01">janvier 1906</date>
[
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF9216F5D4AFFD53F9FE" box="[644,691,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Joly</emphasis>
]”), an illustration (a photo) (“T. LIII (1906). Pl. III”, identified as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF9214E5D742FF34F9DA" authorityName="Linnaeus (1753:" authorityYear="1001" box="[148,212,1563,1588]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="picea">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF9214E5D742FF34F9DA" box="[148,212,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF9214ADD742FE4BF9DB" authority="Trabut." authorityName="Trabut." box="[220,427,1562,1589]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marocana">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF9214ADD742FEADF9DA" box="[220,333,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">marocana</emphasis>
Trabut.
</taxonomicName>
”), accompanied by an explanation (“Deux rameaux d’ 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF92107CD743FAE5F9DA" authority="Trab." authorityName="Trabaud, MPU" authorityYear="1906" box="[1037,1285,1562,1588]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marocana">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF92107CD743FB23F9DA" box="[1037,1219,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Abies marocana</emphasis>
Trab.
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF92117DD742FAC5F9DA" box="[1292,1317,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">gr</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF921145D742FAB8F9DA" box="[1332,1368,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">nat</emphasis>
.”), and some comments with several differences among this new species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF9217FFD766FBE5F9B6" authorityName="Antoine" authorityYear="1841" baseAuthorityName="Boiss." box="[910,1029,1599,1625]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinsapo">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF9217FFD766FBE5F9B6" box="[910,1029,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">A. pinsapo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF92104BD766FB20F9B6" authorityName="de Lannoy ex Carriere, P" authorityYear="1866" box="[1082,1216,1598,1625]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="numidica">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF92104BD766FB20F9B6" box="[1082,1216,1598,1625]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">A. numidica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The protologue also includes a reference to a gathering: “M. Joly, qui a explore dernièrement les montganes de Tétuan et qui y a découvert le 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF9214D2D7DEFE8DF94E" box="[163,365,1671,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Viscaceae" genus="Viscum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Santalales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cruciatum">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF9214D2D7DEFE8DF94E" box="[163,365,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Viscum cruciatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sur l’Olivier, nous a fait parvenir ces jours-ci de la meme region des rameaux d’un 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF921164D7DFFAB3F94E" box="[1301,1363,1670,1696]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF921164D7DFFAB3F94E" box="[1301,1363,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Abies</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B1CFF9214CCD7F3FD26F8DE" blockId="7.[136,1452,1382,2057]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1CFF9214CCD7F3FE66F92A" author="Farjon, A." box="[189,390,1706,1732]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" refId="ref8781" refString="Farjon, A. (2010) A handbook of the world's conifers, vol. 1. Brill Academic Publishers, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1111 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789047430629" type="book" year="2010">Farjon (2010: 112</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1CFF9215E1D7F3FE2AF92A" author="Farjon, A." box="[400,458,1706,1732]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" refId="ref8820" refString="Farjon, A. (2017) A handbook of the world's conifers, 2 nd ed., vol. 1. Brill Academic Publishers, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1153 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004324510" type="book" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
) mentioned “Type not designated”.Among the original elements, the illustration provided in the protologue can be considered original material. In addition, we have located at MPU two relevant specimens that belong to the gathering details mentioned in the protologue. Thus, this material can be treated as 
<typeStatus id="54ED9F8B4B1CFF9210C7D7AAFAF8F8E3" box="[1206,1304,1779,1805]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">syntypes</typeStatus>
(Art. 9.6 and Art. 40 Note 1 of the 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF921509D64EFE47F8DF" box="[376,423,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">ICN</emphasis>
, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC75CD84B1CFF9215AED64FFD5AF8DE" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[479,698,1814,1840]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" refId="ref11897" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B922FD3B4B1CFF92164FD64EFD96F8DE" box="[574,630,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE921294B1CFF9214CCD663FC3CF7E7" blockId="7.[136,1452,1382,2057]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">
The specimen with barcode MPU007733 bears four stems (two of these perhaps are the ones that were photographed and included in the protologue) and leaves, an envelope with leaves, and a label annotated as “Herbier d’Algérie / 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF921576D6DBFE1EF872" authority="Trab." authorityName="Trabaud, MPU" authorityYear="1906" box="[263,510,1922,1949]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marocana">Abies marocana Trab.</taxonomicName>
/ 
<typeStatus id="54ED9F8B4B1CFF921663D6DBFDB0F872" box="[530,592,1922,1948]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Type</typeStatus>
! / Chechaouen / Zone Esp. 
<collectingCountry id="F34161B94B1CFF9217F0D6DAFC2AF873" box="[897,970,1923,1949]" name="Morocco" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Maroc</collectingCountry>
/ leg. 
<collectorName id="26A344FF4B1CFF92107FD6DBFBBFF872" box="[1038,1119,1922,1948]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">A. Joly</collectorName>
1905 / 
<collectorName id="26A344FF4B1CFF9210C2D6DAFAA1F872" box="[1203,1345,1922,1949]" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">D. L. Trabut</collectorName>
” (
<figureCitation id="136D3DAC4B1CFF921128D6DBFA7DF873" box="[1369,1437,1922,1949]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1975,1997]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,190,1951]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[158,1430,190,1951]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Lectotype of Abies marocana Trabaud, MPU (barcode MPU007733). Photography courtesy of Herbarium MPU; reproduced with permission." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605318" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605318/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="38">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). The specimen with barcode MPU007735 bears six stems with leaves and separate leaves, and a label annotated as: “Herbier d’Algérie / 
<taxonomicName id="4C565AAA4B1CFF921504D693FD8FF80A" authority="Trab." authorityName="Trabaud, MPU" authorityYear="1906" box="[373,623,1994,2021]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="7" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marocana">Abies marocana Trab.</taxonomicName>
/ (
